Let’s make Crispy Rice with Spicy Tuna! Doesn’t quite get easier than this! Specially when you get your fresh sushi grade tuna straight from the sushi counter 🙌🏽 thank you @grove.kosher.detroit 

CRISPY RICE WITH SPICY TUNA

Ingredients:
2 cups sushi rice
3 cups water 
Oil, for frying 
2 jalapeños, thinly sliced

Rice vinegar mixture:
3 Tbsp sugar
1/4 cup rice vinegar 
Pinch salt
Microwave then add 
1 t sesame oil 

Spicy tuna:
1 lb minced tuna 
1 Tbsp mayo
1-2 T nap sriracha 
1 tsp sesame oil 

Guacamole: 
3 avocados 
3/4 t salt 

Method:
Cook the sushi rice in the rice maker. 3 cups of water for 2 cups of rice. 

Meanwhile combine the rice vinegar mixture ingredients (sugar should be fully dissolved). Once rice is done pour this mixture and mix well. 

Flatten into a 9x13 pan and freeze for 45 mins. 

Flip rice onto a clean surface and cut into 30 squares. 

Heat oil over medium-high heat. Once hot fry rice squares in batches, for 3-4 mins per side.

Top with guacamole and spicy tuna. Garnish with a slice of jalapeño and enjoy!

Summer burger bowl anyone? Recipe was published a few years ago on @binahmagazine 

Summer Burger Bowl

Ingredients 
1 lb ground beef 
1/2 tsp salt 
1/4 tsp black pepper 
1/4 cup barbecue sauce 
8 wooden skewers

2 6oz package pastrami, chopped
3 tbsp oil 
3 sweet onions, thinly sliced 
1/2 tsp salt 
1/4 cup barbecue sauce 

For the ranch dressing:
1/2 cup mayonnaise 
3/4 tsp fresh lemon juice 
1/4 cup soy milk
1/4 tsp dried parsley or 2 frozen parsley cubes 
1/4 tsp dried dill or 2 frozen dill cubes 
1/4 tsp garlic powder 
1/4 tsp onion powder 
1/4 tsp salt 
1/8 tsp black pepper 

2 hearts romaine lettuce, chopped
1 pint cherry tomatoes, halved 
2-3 avocados, sliced 
3 ears corn on the cob, kernels removed

Method 
Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper; set aside. 

Place ground beef in a bowl season with salt and pepper and mix well. Form a torpedo (kebab-like shape) and pinch with the skewer; place on prepared baking sheet. Brush with barbecue sauce and bake for 20 minutes or until juices run clear. 

Heat up a frying pan over medium heat, add beef fry and sauté for 3 minutes, or until slightly crispy; transfer to a plate, leaving the grease on the pan. 

Add sliced onions, season with salt and sauté for 5 minutes. Add barbecue sauce and continue sautéing until soft and golden and sticky, about 8 minutes. 

Place all the dressing ingredients in a jar and shake until combined. Refrigerate until ready to use. 

To assemble the burger bowl, add lettuce to a bowl, top with a ground beef skewer, crispy beef fry, sautéed onions, cherry tomatoes, sliced avocados, corn and drizzle with ranch dressing.

Let’s make some granola bars together! 

Big Batch Fruit and Nut Bars 
2 cups honey
1 1/3 cup coconut oil 
4 tsp vanilla extract
pinch salt
3 cups chopped almonds 
3 cups chopped pecans
5 oz dried cranberries 
3.4 oz dried blueberries
42oz (12 cups) rolled oats

- Combine honey and coconut oil in a medium pot. Bring to a simmer, and once pot starts bubbling up all over, start the timer for 1 1/2 minutes.

- Remove from heat and stir in the vanilla, and salt. Let it cool down for 10-15 minutes.

- Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.

- Stir in all dry ingredients including dried fruit, nuts, and rolled oats. Mix until evenly coated and press into the prepared pan. Spray a spatula with oil and press down into the pan. Press firmly.

- These granola bars MUST be stored in the fridge, otherwise, they become too soft and will crumble. 

Big Batch Granola Bars 
6 cups quick cooking oats 
3 cup puffed rice
1 ½ cup roughly chopped nuts
1 ½ cup mini chocolate chips 
3/4 cup flaxseed 
3/4 teaspoon salt 
1 ½ cup honey 
1 cup creamy almond butter
3/4 cup coconut oil 
6 teaspoons vanilla extract 

- Preheat oven to 325°F. Line an baking sheet with parchment paper. 
- In a large bowl, stir together the oats, puffed rice, chopped nuts, chocolate chips, flaxseed, and salt.  
- In a medium bowl, stir together the honey, almond butter, coconut oil, and vanilla, until smooth. 
- Pour the wet ingredients into the dry and stir together until well combined. 
- Scoop the mixture into the pan and press it into an even layer, using another piece of parchment paper to firmly press the mixture flat. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, until barely starting to get a little bit of golden color around the edges for chewy granola bars. 

Let the granola bars cool to room temperature in the pan. Then place the pan in the fridge for 1 hour to firm up the granola bars completely. 

Gently lift the parchment paper out of the pan, and slice into granola bars.

ONE POT GNOCCHI BOLOGNESE is to die for 🔥 @whiskbyami 

ONE POT GNOCCHI BOLOGNESE
Meat | Yields 6-8 servings 

Coziness in a bowl. This is one of my families favorite suppers cause after a long busy day, a warm shower and pjs, all my kids want is to cozy up to a warm bowl of yumminess, and this my friends, always hits the spot! The gnocchi comes out pillowy and soft and the bolognese, so simple yet perfectly balanced! Supper in under 20 minutes including prep!

2 Tbsp extra-virgin olive oil
1 small onion, diced (see note) 
1 1/2 lbs ground beef
1 (24oz) jar marinara sauce
1 Tbsp soy sauce
2 Tbsp teriyaki sauce
1 Tbsp red wine vinegar
2 tsp granulated sugar
1 tsp garlic powder
1 tsp salt
1/2 tsp onion powder
1/4 tsp black pepper
2 (16oz) packages classic gnocchi 
Parsley, for garnish, optional 

In a large saucepan, heat oil over medium-high heat. Add onion and sauté for 2-3 minutes, or until translucent. 

Add the ground beef and cook until no longer pink, using a potato masher to break apart any big chunks.

Add marinara sauce and 1/2 jar filled with water; mix well. Add the soy sauce, teriyaki sauce, red wine vinegar, sugar, garlic powder, salt, onion powder and pepper. Mix well and cook for 1 minute.

Add gnocchi and mix well. Bring to simmer, reduce heat to medium and cook, uncovered for 10 minutes. Mix well and garnish with parsley if desired.

LACHMAJEEN (Syrian Meat Pizzas)

Ingredients 
2 Tbsp oil
1 medium onion, finely diced
1 1/2 lbs ground beef
5 Tbsp tomato paste
5 Tbsp ketchup
2 Tbsp granulated sugar
1 tsp allspice
3/4 cup prune butter or oot (tamarind paste) 
1/2 tsp salt
1/4  tsp black pepper
1/4 tsp cayenne pepper, optional
36 frozen mini pizza rounds
pine nuts, optional

METHOD
1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
2. Heat oil in a frying pan over medium heat. Add onion and sauté until soft and slightly brown, about 5 minutes.
3. In a large bowl mix together the ground beef, sautéed onions (including the oil), tomato paste, ketchup, sugar, allspice, prune butter, salt, pepper, and cayenne pepper, if using.
4. Place frozen mini pizza rounds on a parch- ment-lined baking sheet. Top with a heaping tablespoon of the meat mixture. Flatten and top with pine nuts, if using.
5. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

Serve alongside hummus or techinah.

MSHAKELEH
@marblespoon 
Yields 6-8 servings

Ingredients:
1/4 cup oil
1 large onion, chopped
3 lbs cubes stew meat
1 red pepper, chopped
2 large tomatoes, cubed
3 carrots, peeled and sliced
1 small eggplant, peeled and cubed 
2 zucchinis, peeled and cubed
2 potatoes, peeled and cubed

For the sauce: 
2 Tbsp apricot jam
2 Tbsp pomegranate molasses
3 Tbsp granulated sugar
2 Tbsp salt
1 6-oz can tomato paste
2 cups water
1/2 green apple, peeled and very thinly sliced

1. In a large saucepan, heat oil over medium heat. Add onion, stew meat, red pepper, tomatoes, carrots, eggplant, and zucchini. Mix well, then cover and cook for 15 minutes.
2. In a bowl, place all the sauce ingredients and mix well to combine. Pour the sauce over the meat and vegetables. Mix well and bring to a boil. Lower heat and simmer for 1 hour.
3. Add the potatoes and cook for another 30 minutes. Remove from heat, taste, and add more salt if necessary. Serve over rice.

My simplified way of efficiently making mini hot dogs in bulk without stressing yourself out!

Heres what you need to know:
1. I cut through the package because it’s just easier and quicker to do it that way, as opposed to opening the package and slicing each hot dog individually.
2. Wanna use actual mini hotdogs? Go for it — I happen to like the way regular hot dogs taste and it’s cheaper.
3. If you don’t want to make as many, use only one puff pastry sheet and 2 packages of hot dogs.
4. You get 24 hot dogs per package — 8x3=24.
5. You get 40 pieces of puff pastry per sheet, do the math accordingly to how many you need/want to make.
6. Why semi frozen dough? Easier to cut and yields neater rectangles of dough.
7. Use a sharp knife to cut through the dough. 
8. Make sure you do a very thin layer of Dijon mustard. Wanna skip it? You can.
9. You may need to increase or decrease baking time by a bit depending on your oven. Check at the 40 minute mark.
10. Turn baking sheet once so they all brown evenly.
11. Always line baking sheet with parchment or spray with cooking oil or they WILL stick!
12. Wanna add sesame seeds or poppy seeds? Go for it! 
13. You’ll find this method very therapeutic to make, and the ratio of hot dog to dough is perfection!
14. Great addition to your simchas torah charcuterie board!
Enjoy! ❤️

Comfort food during these stressful and scary times… 

ONE POT CREAMY ROSÉ SPAGHETTI 

3 Tbsp avocado oil
3-5 frozen garlic cubes
1 heaping Tbsp paprika in oil 
1 tsp garlic powder 
1 Tbsp sea salt, or more to taste 
1/4 tsp black pepper 
1 6oz can tomato paste 
1 lb spaghetti noodles, snapped in half
5 cups water
2 tsp sugar
2/3 cup heavy cream 
1/2 cup grated parmesan

Heat oil over medium heat in a large nonstick saucepan. Add garlic cubes and sauté until melted. Add paprika in oil and mix well. Add salt, pepper and garlic powder and mix well to incorporate. Add in the tomato paste and stir until combined. Add in spaghetti and stir to coat, make sure all the noodles are well coated with the tomato paste, about 3 minutes. Add in water and sugar, mix well to combine. Bring to a gentle simmer, stirring often so the noodles don’t stick together. Reduce heat to the lowest flame, cover and cook for 13 minutes, stirring a few times in between until pasta is al dente. At this point you can stop here for a non-dairy side dish, if you wish to continue. Add the heavy cream and Parmesan cheese and stir to combine, until well incorporated and the cheese is melted. Enjoy!

SAUTÉED LIVER AND ONIONS
✨Lekoved Shabbos Kodesh✨

3 Tbsp oil 
2 large onion, sliced 
1 lb chicken liver, roughly chopped 
3 tsp paprika in oil or regular paprika 
1 tsp onion powder
1 tsp garlic powder 
2 tsp salt 
1/2 tsp black pepper 
1/4 cup oil
1 Tbsp silan or honey 

Sauté onions in oil in a frying pan over medium heat, until onions are soft and golden. 
Add liver and mix well to combine. Season with paprika in oil, onion powder, garlic powder, salt, pepper. Mix well to incorporate. Add oil and silan, mix well and hear through for about 2 minutes. Serve over hummus if desired.
